# rimba ‚Äî Git Worktree Manager

See AGENTS.md at the repo root for full documentation.

## Top Commands

1. `rimba add <task>` ‚Äî create worktree + branch
2. `rimba list` ‚Äî list all worktrees
3. `rimba status` ‚Äî health overview (dirty, stale, behind)
4. `rimba open <task>` ‚Äî print path or run shortcut (--ide, --agent)
5. `rimba sync [task]` ‚Äî rebase worktree(s) onto main
6. `rimba merge <task>` ‚Äî merge into main and auto-clean up
7. `rimba rename <task> [new-task]` ‚Äî rename a worktree's task, branch, and directory
8. `rimba duplicate <task>` ‚Äî create a new worktree from an existing one
9. `rimba remove <task>` ‚Äî delete worktree + branch
10. `rimba archive <task>` ‚Äî remove worktree, keep branch
11. `rimba restore <task>` ‚Äî recreate a worktree from an archived branch
12. `rimba doctor` ‚Äî diagnose stale git index.lock files
13. `rimba report` ‚Äî aggregate observability timing metrics (p50/p95/mean)
14. `rimba trust` ‚Äî approve committed shell commands
15. `rimba exec <cmd>` ‚Äî run across all worktrees
16. `rimba clean --merged` ‚Äî remove merged worktrees
17. `rimba mcp` ‚Äî start MCP server for AI tool integration

## Workflow Recipes

**New feature:** `rimba add <task>` then work in the worktree directory.
**Monorepo feature:** `rimba add service/task` ‚Äî auto-detects service from repo directories.
**Finish feature:** `rimba merge <task>` (auto-removes worktree).
**Housekeeping:** `rimba status` then `rimba clean --merged`.

## JSON Output

Use `--json` with: list, status, exec, conflict-check, deps status, add, merge, remove, rename, sync, clean, log.
Envelope: `{"version", "command", "data"}` or `{"version", "command", "error", "code"}`.

## Best Practices

- Prefer `archive` over `remove` to keep branches for reference.
- Use `--force` only when you understand the implications.
- Never modify `.rimba/settings.toml` without asking the user.

## MCP Tools

When running inside an MCP-connected agent, prefer the native `mcp__rimba__*` tools over
shelling out to the `rimba` CLI ‚Äî they skip a subprocess round-trip. Fall back to the CLI
when no MCP connection is available.

